1
00:00:08,003 --> 00:00:13,289
What I heard about your punctuality was no exaggeration.

2
00:00:13,544 --> 00:00:17,387
Please. - Thank you, thank you.

3
00:00:17,412 --> 00:00:19,449
For you, Irena, this humble bouquet.

4
00:00:19,929 --> 00:00:21,930
Please, come in. Do come in...

5
00:00:22,150 --> 00:00:26,078
No, don't take it off! No, no...

6
00:00:26,725 --> 00:00:27,387
Absolutely.

7
00:00:27,747 --> 00:00:29,813
I must introduce you to Sabina. Sabinka!

8
00:00:30,593 --> 00:00:33,336
Sabinka! This is my daughter, Sabina.

9
00:00:33,589 --> 00:00:36,675
Mr. Józef, the one about whom you've heard so many good things from me.

10
00:00:36,942 --> 00:00:38,623
You are too kind to me. And your daughter...

11
00:00:40,303 --> 00:00:41,222
is as beautiful as a dream.

12
00:00:43,182 --> 00:00:45,368
I shall allow myself once again to drink to the health of this house.

13
00:00:55,947 --> 00:00:58,411
I know from your mother that you work in the field of culture.

14
00:00:58,717 --> 00:01:00,964
Yes, Sabinka works at a publishing house.

15
00:01:01,947 --> 00:01:03,316
It's a difficult field, I imagine?

16
00:01:04,869 --> 00:01:05,922
One could say that.

17
00:01:07,084 --> 00:01:09,605
I must confess, I have little time for reading.

18
00:01:10,265 --> 00:01:12,605
Life is short, and there is so much to do.

19
00:01:12,802 --> 00:01:14,086
But I have a deep respect for books.

20
00:01:16,348 --> 00:01:19,012
From my mother, who read a great deal.

21
00:01:20,067 --> 00:01:24,866
During the war, when I worked in the finance department, I can swear to you

22
00:01:26,341 --> 00:01:28,461
that with the writer who started on the Belvedere schedule,

23
00:01:29,220 --> 00:01:31,180
I spoke as gently as a child.

24
00:01:31,460 --> 00:01:33,461
She hadn't the slightest clue about accounting.

25
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:36,020
Now, what was her name?...

26
00:01:37,532 --> 00:01:39,759
Zofia Nałkowska? - Of course.

27
00:01:41,682 --> 00:01:44,531
I just need a reminder. So many names in my head...

28
00:01:45,566 --> 00:01:48,396
And you... forgive my curiosity,

29
00:01:49,542 --> 00:01:52,600
do you represent a specific department?

30
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:57,255
Polish poetry.

31
00:01:59,695 --> 00:02:03,056
Ah, you hit the nail on the head!

32
00:02:06,528 --> 00:02:07,515
Poetry...

33
00:02:15,570 --> 00:02:18,101
Much... one might say...

34
00:02:19,873 --> 00:02:24,095
Here’s what I thought. Perhaps you would stay with us, have dinner together...

35
00:02:24,149 --> 00:02:28,282
We are having such a lovely conversation. - Only if I am not taking up your time.

36
00:02:28,682 --> 00:02:29,955
Nonsense, please.

37
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:36,346
Sabinka, tell us, which costume will you wear to the parade?

38
00:02:39,331 --> 00:02:39,791
Alright.

39
00:02:40,467 --> 00:02:42,727
Put on Schumann? - No, no, not now.

40
00:02:42,752 --> 00:02:43,827
First, I'll serve something at the table.

41
00:02:44,335 --> 00:02:47,926
Oh, perhaps you're hungry? - No, no. I'll eat when he leaves.

42
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:53,207
Please, don't be shy.

43
00:02:54,852 --> 00:02:57,079
If I don't answer, I'll just get embarrassed, that's all.

44
00:03:00,665 --> 00:03:02,865
Sixteen times eighteen? - Very easy.

45
00:03:04,286 --> 00:03:07,019
Very easy. Two hundred eighty-eight.

46
00:03:08,748 --> 00:03:11,826
Sabinka, you don't believe me, but I ask you not to pity me.

47
00:03:12,619 --> 00:03:16,266
Right. I'd prefer three-digit numbers. For example...

48
00:03:17,649 --> 00:03:20,082
228 times 314.

49
00:03:23,889 --> 00:03:26,169
228 times 314?

50
00:03:26,708 --> 00:03:29,032
71,592.

51
00:03:33,693 --> 00:03:34,386
Want to check?

52
00:03:37,093 --> 00:03:37,745
I believe you.

53
00:03:41,703 --> 00:03:43,806
I see you have a good eye for people, Sabinka,

54
00:03:44,945 --> 00:03:48,019
because in multiplication, I have no equal. And in division as well...

55
00:03:48,189 --> 00:03:52,427
Mr. Józef, I just don't know if you like jellied pork shanks?

56
00:03:52,473 --> 00:03:54,420
And not just jellied ones, madam.

57
00:03:55,893 --> 00:03:57,407
That's just how I am—I have an appetite.

58
00:03:59,689 --> 00:04:02,416
If the ladies permit... another half glass, because

59
00:04:02,462 --> 00:04:03,536
this cordial is fit for a king...

60
00:04:06,206 --> 00:04:07,829
Well, what do you think of that accountant?

61
00:04:08,176 --> 00:04:12,677
Mom will tell you everything about him. - But... do you like him?

62
00:04:17,406 --> 00:04:22,219
Mrs. Irena, you have a beautiful daughter

63
00:04:23,218 --> 00:04:23,485
and she is incredibly intelligent.

64
00:04:24,325 --> 00:04:28,598
Yes.

65
00:04:32,577 --> 00:04:36,972
If she were to consider me as a potential fiancé,

66
00:04:37,234 --> 00:04:39,135
please tell her that I earn a decent living, and I can earn extra on the side.

67
00:04:39,662 --> 00:04:42,101
With me, she would have more than enough of everything. Only, you understand, I cannot tell her this myself.

68
00:04:42,501 --> 00:04:45,035
But, Józef, I don't need to sing your praises.

69
00:04:45,656 --> 00:04:47,643
You present yourself perfectly well.

70
00:04:48,230 --> 00:04:49,904
Please, help yourself.

71
00:04:50,057 --> 00:04:50,837
And don't look at me,

72
00:04:50,897 --> 00:04:54,827
after one glass my blood pressure rises so much, I can't sleep at all.

73
00:05:10,658 --> 00:05:12,691
Goodness! Has something happened to you? - Nothing of the sort.

74
00:05:13,551 --> 00:05:18,306
I scared you, didn't I? Scared you? I scared you!